title: Whodunnit? (Eclipse Comics)
description:
Like a salmon swimming upstream to return to its birthplace and get its freak on, the Eclipse Comics Upload Project struggles on with 'Whodunnit?', a three-issue mini in which a crime is left unsolved and the first reader to solve it could win a thousand bucks!!! Which was a lot of chedda back in them days!

The series was published in 1986-87, with an issue roughly every six months. It was "hosted" by Jay Endicott, the bailbondsman/secret ID of Crossfire, and written and illustrated by Mark Evanier and Dan Spiegle.

Props to the creative team and the scanners! Get it, seed it!
